column3: 1- Please select the name of your department or major. (If you have a double major, please select your main department.)
column4: 2-Are you currently enrolled in a double major or minor program?
column5: 3- What is your current year of study?
column7: 5- Which of the following best describes your gender identity?
column8: 6- Please indicate your current cumulative GPA (on a 4.00 scale).
column9: 7- Are you currently employed, interning, or working freelance?
column10: 8-I believe my university education adequately prepares me for employment. (1 = Strongly disagree → 5 = Strongly agree)
column11: 9- I am satisfied with the career support and resources provided by my university. (1 = Strongly disagree → 5 = Strongly agree)
column12: 10- I feel confident in my technical and professional skills (e.g., programming, communication, teamwork).
column13: 11- How often do you participate in skill-building activities (courses, workshops, certificates, competitions)?
column14: 12- How active are you in building your professional network (career events, LinkedIn, mentorship, etc.)?
column15: 13- After completing your degree, what is your primary plan?
column16: 14- How confident are you that this gap year will benefit your future career or education?
column17: 15- What do you plan to do during your gap year?
column18: 14- How do you plan to finance your business?
column19: 15- In which sector are you planning to build your business? (Select all options that apply.)
column20: 14- How confident are you in finding a job within 6 months after graduation?
column21: 15- Do you plan to work in a field directly related to your major?
column22: 14- What is your main reason for wanting to pursue a Master’s or PhD degree?
column23: 15- What is the most important criteria for you when choosing a graduate program?
column24: 14- How certain are you about this plan? (1 = Not certain / 5 = Very certain)
column25: 15-When do you expect to start implementing this plan?
column26: 16- Where would you ideally like to work five years from now?
column27: 17- What is your expected net monthly salary for your first full-time job (in TL)? Please specify an approximate range.
column28: 18- Which working style do you prefer for your future job?
column29: 19- Financial security is the single most important aspect when choosing my first job (1 = Strongly disagree → 5 = Strongly agree)
column30: 20- I expect to stay at my first job for less than three years.
column31: 21- I believe my diploma alone will be enough for me to find a good job. (1 = Strongly disagree → 5 = Strongly agree)
column32: 22- I think I might need a second job to maintain a decent standard of living. (1 = Strongly disagree → 5 = Strongly agree)
column33: 23- Having flexibility (remote work, flexible hours) is a priority for me in a job. (1 = Strongly disagree → 5 = Strongly agree)
column34: 24- I am open to considering work opportunities abroad. (1 = Strongly disagree → 5 = Strongly agree)
column35: 25- I think work–life balance is more important than career prestige. (1 = Strongly disagree → 5 = Strongly agree)
column36: 26- I would accept a lower salary for a job that aligns with my values. (1 = Strongly disagree → 5 = Strongly agree)
column37: 27- I believe I need to work more than 40 hours a week to earn a high salary. (1 = Strongly disagree → 5 = Strongly agree)
column38: 28- I believe my long-term career success depends more on luck than on hard work. (1 = Strongly disagree → 5 = Strongly agree)
column39: 29-  Please order the following from 1 (most important) to 5 (least important) according to your priorities. Each number can be used only once. [Work–life balance]
column40: 29-  Please order the following from 1 (most important) to 5 (least important) according to your priorities. Each number can be used only once. [ High salary & benefits]
column41: 29-  Please order the following from 1 (most important) to 5 (least important) according to your priorities. Each number can be used only once. [ Meaningful work (positive social impact)]
column42: 29-  Please order the following from 1 (most important) to 5 (least important) according to your priorities. Each number can be used only once. [ Career stability]
column43: 29-  Please order the following from 1 (most important) to 5 (least important) according to your priorities. Each number can be used only once. [ Autonomy & independence]
